# caveman-commit

Conventional Commits. Why over what. Code block ready to paste.

**Subject:** `type(scope): subject` — types feat/fix/refactor/perf/docs/test/chore/build/ci/style/revert. Imperative. ≤50 chars, cap 72. No period.

**Body:** only if non-obvious why, breaking change, migration, security. Wrap 72. `Closes #N`.

**Never:** "This commit", I/we, AI attribution, emoji (unless project requires), restating filename.

**Always body for:** breaking, security, migration, revert.

Example:
```
feat(api): add GET /users/:id/profile

Mobile needs profile without full user payload for LTE cold-launch.

Closes #128
```
